    "As we will see in our experiments, α ≈ 0.5 aids in long-range tasks.",
    "While the above architecture can support multiple layers stacked successively, we found no benefit to doing so in our experiments.",
    "Furthermore, we found that a small block size of k ≈ 32 solved even long range tasks with ease.",
    "5.1 COMPUTATIONAL COMPLEXITY Let r, d and l be the number of layers, the embedding dimension, and the sequence length respectively of a regular transformer and k the block size of a recurrent transformer.",
    "We note that the computational complexity of the regular transformer is r(l 2 d + ld 2), from which it is easy to see that of the recurrent transformer is r(4dlk + 2ld 2)."
